3. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper involves the use of kinesin driven microtubule motility for on-chip communication. Robotics involves the study of robots and their motion, and hence this paper could belong to this sub-category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves the design and optimization of on-chip kinesin substrates for molecular communication. Systems and control involves the study of systems and their behavior, and hence this paper could belong to this sub-category. 
5. cs.BI (Bioinformatics) - The paper involves the use of kinesin driven microtubule motility for on-chip communication, which is a biological process. Bioinformatics involves the study of biological data and processes, and hence this paper could belong to this sub-category.
